    <primary sortas="a-p20-emu">p20-emu</primary>
  </indexterm>

  <sect2 role="package">
    <title>Introduction to p20-emu</title>

    <para>
      The p20-emu package is a Plexus P/20
      emulator.
    </para>

    
    <itemizedlist spacing="compact">
      <listitem>
        <para>
          Download (HTTP): <ulink url="&p20-emu-download-http;"/>
        </para>
      </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>
   
    <bridgehead renderas="sect3">Additional Downloads</bridgehead>
    <itemizedlist spacing="compact">
      <listitem>
        <para>
          Required ROM 1:
          <ulink url="https://github.com/misterblack1/plexus-p20/raw/refs/heads/main/ROMs/U15-MERGED.BIN"/>
        </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          Required ROM 2:
          <ulink url="https://github.com/misterblack1/plexus-p20/raw/refs/heads/main/ROMs/U17-MERGED.BIN"/>
        </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          Recommended patch:
          <ulink url="&patch-root;/p20-emu/p20-emu-&p20-emu-minor-version;-no-debug.patch"/>
        </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          Recommended patch:
          <ulink url="&patch-root;/p20-emu/p20-emu-&p20-emu-minor-version;-system-roms.patch"/>
        </para>
      </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>

    <bridgehead renderas="sect3">p20-emu Dependencies</bridgehead>

    <bridgehead renderas="sect4">Required</bridgehead>
    <para role="required">
      &unzip;
      (to unpack the distribution)
    </para>

  </sect2>

  <sect2 role="installation">
    <title>Installation of p20-emu</title>

    &extraction-unzip;

    <para>
      Apply a patch to build without any debugging information, which allows
      for a slightly faster binary:
    </para>

<screen><userinput>patch -Np1 -i ../p20-emu-&p20-emu-minor-version;-no-debug.patch</userinput></screen>

    <para>
      Optionally, apply a patch to search for the ROMs in a system-wide
      location and not the current directory:
    </para>

<screen><userinput>patch -Np1 -i ../p20-emu-&p20-emu-minor-version;-system-roms.patch</userinput></screen>

    <para>
      Install p20-emu by running the following
      command:
    </para>

<screen><userinput>make Musashi/m68kops.h &amp;&amp;
make</userinput></screen>

    <para>
      Now, as the &root; user:
    </para>

<screen role="root"><userinput>install -v -Dm755 emu /usr/bin/p20-emu</userinput></screen>

    <para>
      If you have applied the systemwide ROMs patch, install those ROMs as the
      &root; user:
    </para>

<screen role="root"><userinput>install -v -m755 -d /usr/share/p20-emu &amp;&amp;
install -v -m644 ../U15-MERGED.BIN /usr/share/p20-emu &amp;&amp;
install -v -m644 ../U17-MERGED.BIN /usr/share/p20-emu</userinput></screen>

  </sect2>

  <sect2 role="commands">
    <title>Command Explanations</title>

    <para>
      <command>make Musashi/m68kops.h</command>: This command explicitly
      generates a header file used during build time to avoid a race condition.
    </para>

  </sect2>

